# ============================================================
# HomeChain .gitignore — WHITELIST APPROACH
# Strategy: Ignore EVERYTHING, then explicitly allow only
# source code and public documentation.
# This guarantees no private/credential files leak to GitHub.
# ============================================================

# --- IGNORE EVERYTHING ---
*

# --- WHITELIST: Source Code Directories ---
# Allow these folders and all their contents
!app/
!app/**
!cmd/
!cmd/**
!x/
!x/**
!proto/
!proto/**
!third_party/
!third_party/**
!scripts/
!scripts/**
# simulation/ blocked — contains internal .md docs
# Uncomment below when ready to publish simulation code:
# !simulation/
# !simulation/**
!cdeps/
!cdeps/**
!docs/
!docs/**
# NOTE: docs/ contains .md files that may be internal.
# Only allow non-.md files from docs for now.
docs/**/*.md
!.github/
!.github/**

# --- WHITELIST: Root Config Files ---
!go.mod
!go.sum
!Makefile
!Dockerfile
!docker-compose.yml
!buf.yaml
!buf.gen.yaml
!LICENSE
!.gitignore

# --- WHITELIST: Public Documentation ---
!README.md
# NOTE: All other .md files are BLOCKED to prevent leaking
# internal audit/test/ops data. If you want to publish any
# of these later, add them back here:
# !ARCHITECTURE.md
# !WHITEPAPER.md
# !CONTRIBUTING.md
# !SECURITY.md

# --- WHITELIST: Public API Spec ---
!API_SPEC.yaml

# --- EXPLICITLY BLOCKED (even if someone tries git add -f) ---
# These are NEVER pushed to GitHub:
CREDENTIALS.md
*.pem
*.key
*.env
*.env.*
secrets/
keyring-*/
priv_validator_key.json
priv_validator_state.json
node_key.json
mnemonic.txt

# --- LOCAL TOOLING (never push) ---
.code-review-graph/
audits/
analyze_graph.py
audit_graph_query.py
graph_output.txt
CLEANUP_ARTIFACT_v10.md

# --- BUILD ARTIFACTS (never push) ---
build/
*.exe
*.dll
*.so
*.dylib
*.test
*.out
*.db
*.db-journal
*.db-wal
*.db-shm
*.log
*.tmp
*.bak
*.backup
*.tar.gz
*.zip
coverage.*
__debug_bin

# --- IDE / OS JUNK (never push) ---
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
Desktop.ini
